  • Method Details

    • startFuzzingSession

      <R extends org.hl7.fhir.r4.model.Resource> List<FuzzingLogEntry> startFuzzingSession(R resource)
      This is the entry-point to a new Fuzzing-Session. In contrast to fuzzChild(java.lang.String, R), starting a new Fuzzing-Session must ensure, even for small probabilities, the fuzzer finds an entry-point.
      Type Parameters:
      R - concrete type of the resource
      Parameters:
      resource - to be fuzzed
      Returns:
      the fuzzed resource

    • fuzzChild

      default <T extends org.hl7.fhir.r4.model.Type, P> FuzzingLogEntry fuzzChild(P parent, boolean hasType, Supplier<T> typeSupplier)
      Fuzz a child type-element by retrieving via the given supplier
      Type Parameters:
      T - binds the concrete type of the child-element
      P - binds the concrete type of the parent
      Parameters:
      parent - of the type-element where the child element is taken from
      hasType - defines if the parent has already the type-element before applying the supplier
      typeSupplier - to retrieve the child type-element
      Returns:
      a FuzzingLogEntry describing the performed fuzzing operations
